VALUES
(43, 12, 15, 36, 3, 16, 17, 'Fear not, daughter of Sion', 'Connection of Fear and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of not fearing, as seen in ''Fear not'' in each. Additionally, they highlight the presence of the Lord and His saving power, linking the coming King in John to God''s might in Zephaniah.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 15, 10, 16, 2, 2, 'sitting on an ass’s colt', 'Connection of Kingship and Asses', 'This connection highlights the theme of kingship associated with riding on asses. Both passages reference the use of asses in relation to a king, emphasizing the significance of this imagery in the context of royal entry.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 15, 5, 17, 16, 16, 'thy King cometh', 'Connection of Kingship and Humility', 'This connection highlights the theme of kingship, as both passages refer to the nature of a ruler. John 12:15 presents a humble king riding on a colt, while Deuteronomy 17:16 warns against the accumulation of horses, suggesting a reliance on military power rather than humility.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 16, 43, 2, 22, 22, 'remembered they that these things were written of him', 'Disciples'' Understanding of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the disciples'' realization of Jesus'' significance after his resurrection. They reflect a moment of remembrance that leads to belief in the scriptures and Jesus'' words.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 16, 43, 14, 26, 26, 'remembered they that these things were written', 'Disciples'' Remembrance and Teaching', 'This connection highlights the theme of remembrance in both passages. In John 12:16, the disciples remember Jesus'' significance after his glorification, while John 14:26 emphasizes the Holy Spirit''s role in bringing Jesus'' teachings to their remembrance.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 16, 44, 2, 36, 36, 'when Jesus was glorified', 'Disciples'' Understanding of Jesus', 'This connection highlights the recognition of Jesus'' identity. In John, the disciples remember that these things were written of him, while in Acts, it is declared that Jesus is both Lord and Christ, affirming his glorification.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 16, 42, 9, 45, 45, 'understood not', 'Disciples'' Lack of Understanding', 'Both passages emphasize the disciples'' inability to understand Jesus'' words at first. In John, they later remember the significance of events after Jesus is glorified, while in Luke, their lack of understanding is described as being hidden from them.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 16, 42, 18, 34, 34, 'understood not his disciples at the first', 'Disciples'' Lack of Understanding', 'Both passages emphasize the disciples'' inability to comprehend Jesus'' significance at the time. They highlight a moment of realization that comes only after Jesus'' glorification, indicating a shared theme of misunderstanding among the disciples.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 16, 44, 3, 13, 13, 'when Jesus was glorified', 'Glorification of Jesus', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' glorification. In both passages, the disciples and the apostles recognize that Jesus was glorified, linking their understanding of his identity and mission.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 16, 58, 8, 1, 1, 'when Jesus was glorified', 'Disciples'' Understanding of Jesus'' Glory', 'This connection highlights the theme of recognition of Jesus'' glory. In John 12:16, the disciples remember Jesus'' significance after his glorification, while Hebrews 8:1 emphasizes Jesus'' exalted position at the right hand of God, underscoring his role as high priest.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 17, 62, 5, 9, 12, 'bare record', 'Witness and Testimony of Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of witness in both passages. In John 12:17, the people bear record of Jesus'' miracle, while 1 John 5:9-12 discusses the greater witness of God regarding His Son.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 17, 66, 1, 2, 2, 'bare record', 'Witnessing and Testimony Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of bearing witness. Both passages emphasize the act of testifying about significant events, whether it be Lazarus'' resurrection or the word of God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 17, 43, 12, 9, 9, 'raised him from the dead', 'Connection of Lazarus'' Resurrection', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of Lazarus'' resurrection, which draws people to see him and Jesus. The mention of Lazarus in both verses highlights the impact of this miracle on the crowd''s interest.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 17, 43, 19, 35, 35, 'bare record', 'Witnessing and Testimony', 'Both passages emphasize the act of bearing record. In John 12:17, the people bear record of Lazarus'' resurrection, while in John 19:35, the witness affirms the truth of what he has seen.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 17, 44, 1, 22, 22, 'bare record', 'Witnesses of Resurrection', 'This connection highlights the theme of witnessing the resurrection. Both passages emphasize the importance of those who have seen and can testify to Jesus'' miraculous acts, particularly his resurrection.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 17, 44, 5, 32, 32, 'bare record', 'Witnesses of Miraculous Acts', 'This connection highlights the theme of witnessing miraculous events. Both passages emphasize the role of witnesses in affirming divine actions, with John focusing on the resurrection of Lazarus and Acts on the apostles'' testimony of Jesus'' works.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 17, 19, 145, 6, 7, 'bare record', 'Connection of Divine Acts', 'This connection highlights the theme of declaring God''s greatness through miraculous acts. Both passages emphasize the remembrance and proclamation of significant deeds, such as Lazarus'' resurrection and God''s mighty acts.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 18, 43, 12, 11, 11, 'done this miracle', 'Connection of Belief and Miracles', 'Both passages emphasize the impact of Jesus'' miracles on belief. The SOURCE verse highlights that the people gathered due to the miracle, while the TARGET passage notes that many believed on Jesus because of him.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 19, 44, 17, 6, 6, 'the world is gone after him', 'Turning the World', 'Both passages emphasize the impact of Jesus and his followers on the world. In John, the Pharisees lament that ''the world is gone after him,'' while in Acts, the claim is made that they have ''turned the world upside down.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 19, 19, 22, 27, 27, 'the world is gone after him', 'Global Response to God', 'This connection highlights the theme of the world responding to divine authority. In John 12:19, the phrase ''the world is gone after him'' reflects a widespread recognition of Jesus, while Psalms 22:27 speaks of ''all the ends of the world'' turning to the Lord, indicating a universal acknowledgment of God''s sovereignty.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 19, 44, 4, 16, 17, 'the world is gone after him', 'Public Reaction to Miracles', 'Both passages emphasize the public''s response to Jesus and His followers. In John, the Pharisees lament that ''the world is gone after him,'' while in Acts, the leaders acknowledge a ''notable miracle'' that is ''manifest to all.'' This connection highlights the impact of miraculous events on public perception.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 19, 62, 2, 2, 2, 'the world is gone after him', 'World''s Response to Christ', 'This connection highlights the concept of the ''world'' in both passages. In John 12:19, the Pharisees lament that ''the world is gone after him,'' while 1 John 2:2 states that Christ is the propitiation for ''the whole world.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 19, 23, 27, 6, 6, 'the world is gone after him', 'Connection of Global Influence', 'This connection highlights the theme of global impact. In John 12:19, the phrase ''the world is gone after him'' reflects the widespread following of Jesus, while Isaiah 27:6 speaks of Israel filling ''the face of the world with fruit.'' Both passages emphasize a significant influence on the world.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 19, 43, 3, 26, 26, 'the world is gone after him', 'Growing Popularity of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the increasing following of Jesus. In John 12:19, the Pharisees lament that ''the world is gone after him,'' while John 3:26 notes that ''all men come to him.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 19, 43, 17, 21, 21, 'the world is gone after him', 'Unity and Influence of Believers', 'Both passages emphasize the impact of unity among believers. In John 12:19, the Pharisees observe that ''the world is gone after him,'' while John 17:21 expresses a desire for believers to be one, so ''that the world may believe.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 20, 43, 7, 35, 35, NULL, 'Connection of Gentiles in Worship', 'This connection highlights the presence of Gentiles in both passages. In John 12:20, Greeks come to worship, while John 7:35 questions whether Jesus will teach the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 20, 23, 11, 10, 10, NULL, 'Connection of Gentiles Seeking', 'Both passages emphasize the inclusion of Gentiles in worship. John mentions Greeks coming to worship, while Isaiah prophesies that Gentiles will seek the root of Jesse.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 20, 44, 17, 4, 4, NULL, 'Connection of Devout Greeks', 'This connection highlights the presence of Greeks in both passages, indicating their interest in worship and belief in God. Both verses emphasize the role of Greeks in the early Christian community.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 20, 11, 8, 41, 43, 'to worship at the feast', 'Connection of Worship and Strangers', 'Both passages emphasize the inclusion of non-Israelites in worship. John 12:20 mentions Greeks coming to worship, while 1 Kings 8:41-43 discusses a stranger praying toward the temple for God''s name''s sake.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 20, 41, 7, 26, 26, 'Greeks among them', 'Connection of Greek Presence', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of Greeks in the narrative. In John 12:20, Greeks come to worship, while in Mark 7:26, a Greek woman seeks help for her daughter, highlighting the inclusion of Gentiles in the ministry of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
