(43, 12, 44, 43, 13, 20, 20, 'believeth on me, believeth not on me', 'Connection of Belief and Reception', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between belief in Jesus and receiving those He sends. They highlight that believing in Jesus equates to believing in the one who sent Him, and receiving His messengers is akin to receiving Him.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 44, 41, 9, 37, 37, 'but on him that sent me', 'Connection of Belief and Reception', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between belief in Jesus and receiving him as a representative of God. They highlight that to believe in Jesus is to believe in the one who sent him, reinforcing the idea of divine authority.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 44, 60, 1, 21, 21, 'believeth on me, believeth not on me', 'Faith in God through Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize belief in God through Jesus. John 12:44 highlights belief in the one who sent Jesus, while 1 Peter 1:21 states that believers have faith in God through Jesus'' resurrection.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 44, 20, 8, 1, 1, 'He that believeth on me', 'Wisdom and Belief Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of calling and response. Both passages emphasize a voice that cries out, inviting belief and understanding.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 44, 23, 55, 1, 3, 'believeth on me', 'Invitation to Belief and Life', 'This connection highlights the invitation to come and believe in God, as seen in both passages. John emphasizes belief in Jesus as belief in the one who sent him, while Isaiah invites all to come and receive life-giving sustenance.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 45, 43, 14, 9, 10, 'he that seeth me seeth him', 'Connection of Seeing the Father', 'Both passages emphasize the idea that seeing Jesus is equivalent to seeing the Father. This connection highlights the unity between Jesus and the Father in their divine nature and works.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 45, 47, 4, 6, 6, 'seeth him that sent me', 'Connection of Light and Revelation', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeing and understanding divine truth. Both passages emphasize the revelation of God through Jesus Christ, portraying Him as the light that reveals God''s glory.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 45, 51, 1, 15, 15, 'seeth me seeth him that sent me', 'Connection of Divine Visibility', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeing God through Christ. Both passages emphasize that Jesus reveals the nature of God, with John stating that seeing Him means seeing the one who sent Him, and Colossians describing Jesus as the image of the invisible God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 45, 43, 12, 41, 41, 'seeth me seeth him that sent me', 'Connection of Seeing and Glory', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of seeing. In John 12:45, seeing Jesus equates to seeing the one who sent him, while John 12:41 refers to Isaiah seeing the glory of the Lord, linking the act of seeing to divine revelation.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 45, 58, 1, 3, 3, 'seeth him that sent me', 'Connection of Divine Representation', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Jesus and God. John 12:45 states that seeing Jesus is akin to seeing the one who sent him, while Hebrews 1:3 describes Jesus as the express image of God''s person.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 45, 62, 5, 20, 20, 'seeth him that sent me', 'Connection of Divine Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Jesus and God. John 12:45 highlights seeing Jesus as seeing the one who sent him, while 1 John 5:20 speaks of knowing the true God through Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 46, 43, 8, 12, 12, NULL, 'Connection of Light in John', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus as the light of the world, indicating that belief in Him leads to illumination and life. The phrases ''light'' and ''darkness'' are central themes in both verses, highlighting the transformative power of following Jesus.', 'theme', 0.692, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 46, 19, 36, 9, 9, 'light into the world', 'Light and Life Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of light as essential for understanding and life. John 12:46 speaks of Jesus as a light, while Psalms 36:9 describes seeing light through God''s presence, linking belief in Jesus to spiritual illumination.', 'theme', 0.587, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 46, 43, 9, 5, 5, 'light into the world', 'Light of the World Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of Jesus as light. John 12:46 states He came as a light, while John 9:5 affirms His identity as the light of the world.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 46, 23, 42, 7, 7, 'should not abide in darkness', 'Light and Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of bringing people out of darkness. John speaks of being a light to prevent abiding in darkness, while Isaiah mentions bringing those who sit in darkness out of prison. This connection highlights the transformative power of light in overcoming darkness.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 46, 44, 26, 18, 18, 'light into the world', 'Light and Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the transition from darkness to light, highlighting the role of belief in Jesus as a source of illumination and transformation. The SOURCE verse presents Jesus as the light, while the TARGET passage describes the act of turning from darkness to light.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 46, 42, 1, 76, 79, 'light into the world', 'Light and Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of light coming into darkness. John 12:46 speaks of Jesus as a light, while Luke 1:79 mentions giving light to those in darkness.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 46, 40, 4, 16, 16, 'light into the world', 'Light in Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of light overcoming darkness. John 12:46 speaks of Jesus as the light, while Matthew 4:16 describes people in darkness seeing great light, highlighting the transformative power of this light.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 47, 43, 3, 17, 17, 'not to judge the world', 'Purpose of Jesus'' Mission', 'Both passages emphasize that Jesus was sent not to judge but to save the world. This connection highlights the consistent theme of salvation over condemnation in His mission.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 47, 43, 8, 15, 16, NULL, 'Judgment and Salvation Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of not judging others. John 12:47 states, ''I judge him not,'' while John 8:15 reinforces, ''I judge no man.'' This connection highlights a consistent theme of Jesus'' mission to save rather than condemn.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 47, 54, 1, 15, 16, 'to save the world', 'Purpose of Christ''s Coming', 'This connection highlights the shared theme of Jesus'' mission to save rather than judge. Both passages emphasize that Christ came into the world to save sinners and the world, reflecting His purpose of mercy and salvation.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 12, 47, 62, 4, 14, 14, 'to save the world', 'Connection of Salvation Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the mission of Jesus as the Savior of the world. John 12:47 highlights His purpose to save rather than judge, while 1 John 4:14 explicitly states that the Father sent the Son to be the Savior.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
